==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waterway
<hw>Wa"ter*way`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>Heavy plank or timber extending fore and aft the whole length of a
vessel's deck at the line of junction with the sides, forming a channel
to the scuppers, which are cut through it. In iron vessels the waterway
is variously constructed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water way</ent>⟦br⟧
